HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1131
By Gant
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Robert Randle Roll of
Memphis.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Robert Randle Roll; and
WHEREAS, Robert Roll was a beloved friend and neighbor who did his utmost to
improve the well-being of all who were blessed to know him; and
WHEREAS, the son of Bobby Lee and Dorthy Spencer Roll, Mr. Roll was born and
raised in Memphis, where he graduated from Central High School in 1983; and
WHEREAS, Robert Roll went on to continue his education at Middle Tennessee State
University, where he further developed the work ethic and determination that guided him
throughout his professional life; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Roll devoted twenty-three years of service to Seabrook Wallcoverings,
serving the company as a manager of a retail store and later transitioning to outside sales,
where he truly excelled; his dedication, leadership, and ability to build lasting relationships
earned him the respect of colleagues and customers alike; and
WHEREAS, Robert Roll then transitioned to a career in the insurance industry; he
became a respected insurance agent and vice president of Boyle Insurance Agency, in which
role he was known for his integrity, professionalism, and genuine concern for his clients; Mr.
Roll took great pride in helping others protect what mattered most to them; and
WHEREAS, a man with many passions, Mr. Roll was an avid golfer and sports fan; he
loved cheering on the Tennessee Volunteers, the Tennessee Titans, and the St. Louis
Cardinals, and he found great peace in sitting on his porch with his dogs, listening to classic 70s
rock; and
HJR1131
015493
- 1 -

WHEREAS, he was also deeply devoted to his family and always endeavored to remain
true to family values of the highest order; he cherished spending time with his family, from
holidays to Sunday dinners and vacations to the beach; and
WHEREAS, Robert Roll is survived by his wife, Nancy Pepple Roll; his son, Peyton
(Kaylee); his granddaughter, Murphy; his sisters, Jan Murphey, Gina (Randy) Hyneman, and
Connie (Jim) Holloway; and several nieces and nephews; and
WHEREAS, in addition to his parents, he was preceded in death by his sister, Marilyn
Thomas, and his son, Parker Roll; and
WHEREAS, throughout his many worthy endeavors, Robert Roll distinguished himself
as a beacon of kindness, dedication, and loyalty; and
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pay tribute to the bountiful life of this exceptional
Tennessean; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor the memory of Robert Randle Roll, reflecting fondly upon his
ability to live the examined life with courage and conviction.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that we extend our sympathy and condolences to the
family and friends of Mr. Roll.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
